laboratory_examinations.findings: Minor atelectatic changes at lung bases; normal heart size; evidence of prior liver resections; small amount of nonspecific fluid adjacent to liver; atrophic pancreas; bilateral renal cysts; significant bowel wall thickening at the terminal ileum with diverticuli; heavy atherosclerotic calcifications in the abdominal aorta; no free air in abdomen; sigmoid diverticulosis noted.
